Citations
Date: 0/6/1982
Source: NZ Dairy Exporter
Author:
Vol / Page: 5
Edition:
Quote: As a rule, use BI for breeding and production index for culling. Effective BIs and PIs are not available unless a farmer herd-tests and identifies progeny through the local livestock or breed association. When looking at cows' production, remember that PIs rank cows within a herd.
